    <title type="html"><![CDATA[A Slick jQuery Slider Plugin]]></title>
    <link href="http://JoeWoodward.github.com/joewoodward/blog/2012/09/22/a-slick-jquery-slider-plugin/"/>
    <updated>2012-09-22T00:42:00+01:00</updated>
    <id>http://JoeWoodward.github.com/joewoodward/blog/2012/09/22/a-slick-jquery-slider-plugin</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<script src="http://JoeWoodward.github.com/joewoodward//ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.8.1/jquery.min.js"></script>


<script type="text/javascript" src="http://JoeWoodward.github.com/joewoodward/javascripts/slick_slider.js"></script>


<p><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="http://JoeWoodward.github.com/joewoodward/stylesheets/slick_slider.css"></p>

<div id="slick-slider">
<ul id="menu">
<li data-index="1" class="active">
Overview
</li>
<li data-index="2">
Markup and CSS
</li>
<li data-index="3">
jQuery
</li>
</ul>
<div id="slides-window">
<div id="slides">
<div class="slide active" id="1">
<div class="h1-border">
<h1 class="diagonal-corners">Important! All content must be wrapped within a div!</h1>
</div>
<div class="divider"></div>
<h2>What do we need?</h2>
<h3>Mark Up</h3>
<ol>
<li>A containing div (<b>#slick-slider</b>)</li>
<li>Menu items with <b>data-index</b> attributes relating to the position of the corresponding content</li>
<li>A <b>#slides-window</b> div with overflow hidden to view the current slide through while hiding the others</li>
<li>The <b>#slides</b> div to hold your slides</li>
<li>Your slides in divs with the <b>.slide</b> class and an ID of the position. i.e. the <b>first</b> div should be <b>#1</b>, the <b>second #2</b>, <b>third #3</b></li>
<li>The first menu item and the first slide should be assigned the class <b>.active</b></li>
</ol>
<h3>Some CSS</h3>
<ol>
<li>We need the slides in a row, to achieve this the <b>#slides</b> div needs to have <b>10000% width</b> and <b>overflow hidden</b></li>
<li>We can then <b>float left</b> all of the <b>.slide</b>[s] and give them a <b>width</b> of <b>1%</b>, this keeps the slider responsive</li>
<li>Then we need to <b>hide</b> the <b>overflow</b> for the <b>#slides-window</b> and give it some <b>padding</b></li>
</ol>
<h3>The jQuery</h3>
<ol>
<li>
Add the slick slide file to your website <a href="http://JoeWoodward.github.com/joewoodward/downloads/code/javascripts/jQuery.slickSlider.js.zip">from here</a>
</li>
<li>You can supply <b>fade</b> and <b>transitionDuration</b> arguments to the <b>initSlickSlider()</b> function. Defaults = {fade: true, transitionDuration: 300}</li>
<li>Initialise the Slick Slider on the #menu li&#8217;s, i.e. <b>$(&#8216;#slick-slider #menu li&#8217;).initSlickSlider({fade: false, transitionDuration: 800});</b></li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="slide" id="2">
<h3>Let&#8217;s take a look at the markup</h3>
<br />
<div><script src='https://gist.github.com/3786718.js?file=slick_slider.html'></script>
<noscript><pre><code>&lt;div id=&quot;slick-slider&quot;&gt;
  &lt;ul id=&quot;menu&quot;&gt;
    &lt;li data-index=&quot;1&quot; class=&quot;active&quot;&gt;
      Item 1
    &lt;/li&gt;

    &lt;li data-index=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
      Item 2
    &lt;/li&gt;

    &lt;li data-index=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
      Item 3
    &lt;/li&gt;

    &lt;li data-index=&quot;4&quot;&gt;
      Item 4
    &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/ul&gt;

  &lt;div id=&quot;slides-window&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div id=&quot;slides&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot; id=&quot;1&quot;&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;Slide 1&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Some Content Would Go In Here&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot; id=&quot;2&quot;&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;Slide 2&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Some Content Would Go In Here&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;

      &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot; id=&quot;3&quot;&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;Slide 3&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Some Content Would Go In Here&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;

      &lt;div class=&quot;slide&quot; id=&quot;4&quot;&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;Slide 4&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Some Content Would Go In Here&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre></noscript></div>

<h3>And the necessarry CSS</h3>
<br />
<div><script src='https://gist.github.com/3786718.js?file=slick_slider.css'></script>
<noscript><pre><code>#slides-window {
  overflow: hidden;
  padding: 20px;
}

#slides {
  width: 10000%;
  overflow: hidden;
  height: 0;
}

.slide {
  width: 1%;
  float: left;
  margin-right: 0.2%;
}</code></pre></noscript></div>

</div>
<div class="slide" id="3">
<h3>Here&#8217;s the code</h3>
<br />
<div><script src='https://gist.github.com/3786718.js?file=jQuery.slickSlider.js'></script>
<noscript><pre><code>$.fn.initSlickSlider = function(options){
  var goToMargin;

  // #TODO modulate slide function for fade only!

  // set default options
  var settings = jQuery.extend({
    transitionDuration: 300, fade: true
  }, options);

  // $(this) should be a group of li's
  var menu = $(this);

  // set the #slides-window's height to the first .slide's height
  $(this).closest('div').find('#slides').animate({height: $(this).closest('div').find('#1').height()}, 800);

  // fade content-area away and new one in
  $(menu).live('click', function(event) {

    // get the parent div incase there are multiple tabbed sliders on one page
    var parent = $(this).closest('div');

    // get the ID of the current slide
    var currentId = parseInt($(this).siblings('.active').data('index'));

    // get the ID of the div that will be positioned in view
    var newId = parseInt($(this).data('index'));

    // get the div currently in view
    var currentSlide = $(parent).find('#' + currentId);

    // get the #slides div
    var slides = $(parent).find('#slides');

    //  get the current slide
    var newSlide = $(slides).find('#' + (newId));

    var height = $(this).data('height');
    height = height === undefined ? $(newSlide).height() : height;

    $(slides).children().stop().css('opacity', 1);

    var range;
    var time;

    if(settings.fade === true) {
      if(currentId &gt; newId) {
        range = currentId - newId;
        time = (settings.transitionDuration / range) * 0.8;
        for(var i = currentId; i &gt; newId; i--) {
          $('#' + i).delay(time * (range - (i - newId))).animate({opacity:0}, time, 'linear');
        }
      } else {
        range = newId - currentId;
        time = (settings.transitionDuration / range) * 0.8;
        for(var i = currentId; i &lt; newId; i++) {
          $('#' + i).delay(time * (range - (newId - i))).animate({opacity:0}, time, 'linear');
        }
      }
    }

    goToMargin = -((newId - 1) * 120);

    // slide the #slides div to the correct posisiton and change the height
    $(slides).stop().animate({height: height, marginLeft: goToMargin + '%'}, settings.transitionDuration, 'linear', function(){
      $(slides).children().css('opacity', 1);
    });

    // deactivate the current slide
    $(currentSlide).removeClass('active');

    // activate the new slide
    $(newSlide).addClass('active');

    // set the menu button to active
    $(this).addClass('active').siblings().removeClass('active');
  });
};

$(window).load(function(){
  $('#menu li').initSlickSlider({transitionDuration: 800});
});</code></pre></noscript></div>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

]]></content>
